03:35.937 --> 03:38.322
(gasps)

03:38.324 --> 03:41.058
(shuddering breaths)

03:43.862 --> 03:45.595
(siren whoops)

03:49.567 --> 03:51.452
Who's the guy?
What?

03:51.454 --> 03:52.903
You only file when
there's a problem

03:52.905 --> 03:55.906
with a guy.
That is not true.

03:55.908 --> 03:58.158
(Catherine sighs)

03:59.194 --> 04:01.495
Okay, okay, fine.

04:01.497 --> 04:03.280
I knew it; I knew
there was a guy.

04:03.282 --> 04:05.382
"Was" being the operative word.

04:05.384 --> 04:07.784
Apparently, I got myself
into yet another

04:07.786 --> 04:10.921
complicated non-relationship
that I think is going somewhere,

04:10.923 --> 04:13.340
only to discover
it is going nowhere.

04:13.342 --> 04:15.459
Okay, well, first of all,
if he's not into you,

04:15.461 --> 04:17.428
he's an idiot,
and second-- who is he?

04:17.430 --> 04:18.978
Doesn't matter.

04:18.981 --> 04:21.598
From now on, I am
sticking to simple.

04:21.600 --> 04:23.517
Simple, like your dad
marrying someone young enough

04:23.519 --> 04:25.769
to be your sister?

04:26.688 --> 04:29.406
Oh, God. Dress fitting.

04:29.408 --> 04:31.909
Brooke forgot to take your shoes
when she left this morning.

04:31.911 --> 04:34.478
She says she'll meet you
at the bridal salon at 1:00.

04:34.480 --> 04:37.247
Okay, I meant to call, but since
Heather's away in Atlantic City,

04:37.249 --> 04:38.648
I thought we
could reschedule.

04:38.650 --> 04:40.584
You know, dresses are
much more her thing.

04:40.586 --> 04:42.819
Catherine, I wish you'd
just give Brooke a chance.

04:42.821 --> 04:44.204
I have.

04:44.206 --> 04:45.956
You haven't spent
more than ten minutes

04:45.958 --> 04:48.208
in the same room with her
since the engagement party.

04:48.210 --> 04:50.110
(sighs)

04:50.112 --> 04:52.513
Great. So I'll see you
at dinner tonight.

04:52.515 --> 04:55.215
(sighs, groans)
The reservation's for four,

04:55.217 --> 04:57.801
so if you can't bear the
thought of being trapped alone

04:57.803 --> 04:59.242
with just the two of us,
invite someone.

04:59.267 --> 04:59.888
Mm.

04:59.889 --> 05:02.056
Like that nice man from
the engagement party.

05:02.058 --> 05:03.357
Brooke really
hit it off with him.

05:03.359 --> 05:05.392
Evan?
You talking about me?

05:05.394 --> 05:07.528
Mr. Chandler.
Good to see you.

05:07.530 --> 05:10.948
How would you like to save Cat
and come to dinner tonight?

05:10.950 --> 05:12.533
Dad.
No. It would

05:12.535 --> 05:14.201
be my pleasure.
What time?

05:14.203 --> 05:15.486
Hello. The person
that you are

05:15.488 --> 05:16.686
talking about is right here.

05:16.688 --> 05:18.872
7:30. At Per Se.
Still here.

05:18.874 --> 05:20.524
We'll be there.
Terrific.

05:22.711 --> 05:24.545
It means a lot to me.

05:24.547 --> 05:25.996
And to Brooke.

05:25.998 --> 05:28.865
All right, see you tonight.
Okay.

05:28.867 --> 05:32.419
Okay, before I enumerate
all of the ways that that was wrong,

05:32.421 --> 05:34.579
we should probably talk about
what happened the other night.

05:34.604 --> 05:35.340
Agreed.

05:35.341 --> 05:37.725
We got a dead body
down in SoHo.

05:37.727 --> 05:39.176
Looks like
we'll have to continue

05:39.178 --> 05:40.544
this conversation at dinner.

05:51.689 --> 05:54.608
I'm telling you, your dad
did you a huge favor.

05:54.610 --> 05:56.410
I am not having this
conversation right now.

05:56.412 --> 05:58.028
Things go south
with Mr. Complicated,

05:58.030 --> 06:00.781
he gets you a date with Evan.
It is not a date.

06:00.783 --> 06:02.833
Dinner at Per Se?
That's the definition of a date.

06:02.835 --> 06:05.085
You know what I'm thinking,
I'm thinking you're so hung up

06:05.087 --> 06:07.121
on the other guy
'cause he rejected you,

06:07.123 --> 06:08.533
and there's nothing more
tempting than rejection.

06:08.558 --> 06:09.424
That is ridiculous.

06:09.425 --> 06:11.358
That's Psych 101.
Besides, Evan's a cute guy

06:11.360 --> 06:13.177
and clearly
likes you.

06:13.179 --> 06:15.129
Okay.

06:15.131 --> 06:18.748
Nicholas Varkas, 26,
Queens address.

06:18.750 --> 06:21.702
Nicholas is an artist.
Any evidence of a break-in?

06:21.704 --> 06:24.254
No. No forced entry,
nothing missing.

06:24.256 --> 06:26.546
And the woman who found
the body said that there was

06:26.571 --> 06:27.942
some art opening tonight.

06:27.943 --> 06:30.611
It looks like they're
still having it.

06:30.613 --> 06:32.863
Well, if we let them,
they'd put a velvet rope

06:32.865 --> 06:34.615
around him and call it
an "installation""

06:34.617 --> 06:36.266
Are you Lauren Harris?

06:36.268 --> 06:39.153
Yeah. The other officers told me
I can keep working.

06:39.155 --> 06:41.655
We have 200 people
coming here in ten hours.

06:41.657 --> 06:42.956
The show must go on?

06:42.958 --> 06:43.957
He's not gonna cancel.

06:43.959 --> 06:45.125
"He" being...?

06:45.127 --> 06:46.827
Marco. The owner.
How many people

06:46.829 --> 06:49.046
have access to this gallery?
Usually,

06:49.048 --> 06:51.381
just me, Marco
and a few of the assistants,

06:51.383 --> 06:54.418
but Nicholas was here loading in
the final pieces last night.

06:54.420 --> 06:55.969
If that door
was left propped open,

06:55.971 --> 06:57.654
someone could've come in
from the alley.

06:57.656 --> 06:59.506
Can you think of anyone
who'd have a beef with him?

06:59.508 --> 07:01.124
I only met him a few times.

07:01.126 --> 07:03.227
EVAN:
Cat, Tess.

07:04.479 --> 07:06.563
EVAN:
Shot in the back.

07:06.565 --> 07:08.682
Two bullets,
low-caliber weapon.

07:08.684 --> 07:11.635
But the way he fell, he wasn't
running away from someone.

07:11.637 --> 07:13.403
So either someone
snuck up on him...

07:13.405 --> 07:16.273
Or whoever he was, he didn't
think they were a threat.

07:16.275 --> 07:18.075
I also found
some white cotton fibers.

07:18.077 --> 07:21.028
It's a long shot, but I could
run them back to the lab now.

07:21.030 --> 07:22.696
You two lovebirds go ahead.

07:22.698 --> 07:25.482
I'm gonna check out
the art in the bathroom.

07:25.484 --> 07:27.534
CATHERINE:
Okay, look, you don't have

07:27.536 --> 07:29.753
to come to dinner--
my dad put you on the spot.

07:29.755 --> 07:32.250
Not that it's a big deal
or anything, but the last

07:32.275 --> 07:33.694
thing I want to be doing
is having dinner

07:33.695 --> 07:35.739
with another murky,
undefined situation.

07:35.794 --> 07:37.211
This isn't murky, Cat.

07:37.213 --> 07:38.629
It's simple, okay?

07:38.631 --> 07:41.715
I'll pick you up at 7:00.

07:41.717 --> 07:45.302
Unless you don't think you can
handle yourself around me.

07:47.222 --> 07:48.689
Of course I can handle myself.

07:48.691 --> 07:50.674
It's just, after
the incident at my party...

07:50.676 --> 07:52.359
You mean when
you kissed me?

07:52.361 --> 07:55.362
You kissed <i>me.</i>
Your cheeks are turning red.

07:55.364 --> 07:57.030
(sighs)

07:57.032 --> 07:59.233
It's just, I don't want
to complicate things now.

07:59.235 --> 08:02.319
We're friends, we work together,
and I know what that's like,

08:02.321 --> 08:04.988
to think that someone
has feelings for you when...

08:04.990 --> 08:06.957
There are absolutely
no feelings.

08:06.959 --> 08:09.543
It was just one kiss.
Right.

08:09.545 --> 08:12.496
Just one, completely
meaningless...

08:12.498 --> 08:14.915
kiss.

08:17.218 --> 08:20.804
I'll pick you up at 7:00.

08:24.642 --> 08:26.810
(sighs)

