08:39.347 --> 08:42.162
WOMAN: <i>Nicholas was broken up</i>
<i>about a girl.</i>

08:42.163 --> 08:44.296
He met her
at an art opening.

08:44.298 --> 08:46.548
She ended it
a couple of weeks ago.

08:46.550 --> 08:48.083
But it wasn't serious.

08:48.085 --> 08:49.718
I never met her.

08:49.720 --> 08:51.337
Did your son mention a name?

08:51.339 --> 08:52.471
Was there anyone

08:52.473 --> 08:53.922
he wasn't getting along with?

08:53.924 --> 08:56.225
He had a fight, um...

08:56.227 --> 08:59.395
on the phone...
two nights ago.

08:59.397 --> 09:01.430
About prices.

09:01.432 --> 09:03.232
Prices of
his paintings,

09:03.234 --> 09:05.434
I guess.

09:05.436 --> 09:07.486
He was yelling.

09:07.488 --> 09:09.571
It woke me up.

09:13.326 --> 09:16.695
11:15 p.m., Nicholas made a call
to the Marco Giconni Gallery.

09:16.697 --> 09:20.949
Our still conspicuously
absent gallery owner.

09:20.951 --> 09:23.151
Hmm.

09:23.153 --> 09:25.654
He may explain what I found
in Nicholas's bank account--

09:25.656 --> 09:27.673
not much.
I thought he'd be loaded--

09:27.675 --> 09:29.508
selling paintings
for five grand a pop.

09:29.510 --> 09:30.959
The standard gallery
commission's 50%,

09:30.961 --> 09:32.661
but Nicholas was
only making deposits

09:32.663 --> 09:34.480
for a couple hundred
here and there.

09:34.482 --> 09:36.265
If Marco was cheating Nicholas
out of his cut,

09:36.267 --> 09:38.217
maybe he went there
to confront him.

09:38.219 --> 09:40.168
(phone beeps)

09:40.170 --> 09:41.553
(groans):
Oh, its' my Dad.

09:41.555 --> 09:43.272
Checking in about
your big date?

09:43.274 --> 09:45.474
It is not a date.
Look, I know

09:45.476 --> 09:47.342
you're still holding out
for Complicated Guy,

09:47.344 --> 09:49.945
but you and Evan were both
blushing when I left.

09:49.947 --> 09:51.113
Okay, that's just because...

09:51.115 --> 09:52.948
(Catherine clears her throat)

09:52.950 --> 09:55.284
Okay.

09:56.286 --> 09:58.904
(whispers):
Okay.

09:58.906 --> 10:00.072
Yeah...

10:00.074 --> 10:01.657
he kissed me

10:01.659 --> 10:04.576
at my birthday party,
in the photo booth.

10:04.578 --> 10:05.794
What are we, strangers?

10:05.796 --> 10:07.162
How could you hold out
on me like that?

10:07.164 --> 10:08.747
It was not that big a deal.

10:10.834 --> 10:12.251
Okay, i-it's a mi...

10:12.253 --> 10:13.702
it's a minor big deal.

10:13.704 --> 10:15.954
Well, I'm confused.
Is it big or minor?

10:15.956 --> 10:17.389
(phone chimes)

10:17.391 --> 10:19.224
No, no, no, no.
Dinner's in five hours.

10:19.226 --> 10:20.259
Your dad can wait.

10:20.261 --> 10:21.810
It's not my dad.

10:21.812 --> 10:23.545
It is my soon-to-be step...

10:23.547 --> 10:26.148
thingy reminding me
of my dress fitting.

10:26.150 --> 10:27.399
This conversation's
not over.

10:27.401 --> 10:28.767
Oh, I'm glad you
feel that way,

10:28.769 --> 10:30.352
because you're
coming with me.

10:30.354 --> 10:32.721
And you're driving.
What?!

10:32.723 --> 10:35.607
Really? Because you don't
have to, I mean...

10:35.609 --> 10:37.225
Well, yeah, I'd love
to go for coffee.

10:37.227 --> 10:39.228
Ugh, I'm in desperate need
of caffeine,

10:39.230 --> 10:41.130
and I should probably
eat something

10:41.132 --> 10:43.532
that hasn't been microwaved
in a petri dish.

10:43.534 --> 10:47.086
The coffee at the campus diner
is guaranteed to kill

10:47.088 --> 10:50.139
any bacteria you may have
consumed with your lunch.

10:50.141 --> 10:51.540
(laughing)

10:51.542 --> 10:53.926
VINCENT: Hey, JT, I need
help with these

10:53.928 --> 10:55.310
numbers, man.

10:55.312 --> 10:56.712
Who's that?

10:56.714 --> 10:58.263
Uh, no one. I got to go.

10:58.265 --> 10:59.264
See you there?

10:59.266 --> 11:00.749
Okay, bye.

11:00.751 --> 11:02.768
Blood pressure is fine,
so please...

11:02.770 --> 11:04.937
please tell me why

11:04.939 --> 11:08.023
I can't remember
what happened last night.

11:08.025 --> 11:10.726
I don't know,
but for the third time,

11:10.728 --> 11:12.895
everything's normal.

11:12.897 --> 11:15.430
I woke up on the top
of Brooklyn Bridge.

11:15.432 --> 11:17.316
I'm not saying
that's not a problem.

11:17.318 --> 11:18.400
Come on, man.
(sighs)

11:18.402 --> 11:20.652
This has never happened before.

11:20.654 --> 11:22.070
Okay, let's trace it back.

11:22.072 --> 11:25.157
What were you doing
before your sleepwalk

11:25.159 --> 11:26.658
down non-memory lane?

11:26.660 --> 11:28.494
I was headed
to Catherine's and...

11:29.329 --> 11:30.779
What?

11:30.781 --> 11:31.914
What'd she
do now?

11:31.916 --> 11:33.949
Nothing.

11:33.951 --> 11:35.968
She must have
done something.

11:35.970 --> 11:39.505
Wait-- is this about her kissing
that guy the other night?

11:40.507 --> 11:42.391
You were thinking
about Catherine

11:42.393 --> 11:43.959
and some jerk in a lip-lock.

11:43.961 --> 11:46.895
Adrenaline kicks in,
your heart rate increases--

11:46.897 --> 11:48.514
long story short,

11:48.516 --> 11:51.850
you fugued-out
because you're jealous.

11:52.635 --> 11:54.436
"Fugued-out"?

11:54.438 --> 11:57.022
Fugue-- you're up
and walking around but...

11:57.024 --> 11:58.273
it's like you
got amnesia.

11:58.275 --> 11:59.525
Okay, wait.

11:59.527 --> 12:02.644
Jealousy cannot
cause memory loss.

12:02.646 --> 12:03.996
Besides...

12:03.998 --> 12:06.865
I don't have a right
to be jealous anyway.

12:06.867 --> 12:08.500
Free advice?

12:08.502 --> 12:11.787
Take a chance and tell her
how you feel.

12:11.789 --> 12:13.205
Okay, wait.

12:13.207 --> 12:15.507
Wait, wait, wait.
Who are you right now?

12:15.509 --> 12:17.759
Look, I know I've been
the president

12:17.761 --> 12:20.546
of the "Stay Away
from Catherine Club," but...

12:20.548 --> 12:22.681
she's only gonna wait
for you for so long

12:22.683 --> 12:24.816
before she moves on.

12:30.339 --> 12:31.990
(sighs quietly)

12:31.992 --> 12:34.643
♪

12:36.763 --> 12:40.482
♪ It'll be just
a matter of time ♪

12:40.484 --> 12:43.202
♪ Before you're crawling...

12:43.204 --> 12:45.320
(sighs)

12:45.322 --> 12:47.039
Okay. You ready?

12:47.041 --> 12:49.357
I can't wait to see it on you.
(teacup clinks)

13:00.136 --> 13:02.504
So, what do you think?

13:04.173 --> 13:05.173
It's nice.

13:05.175 --> 13:06.842
It's a lovely shape.

13:06.844 --> 13:08.977
And it will match
the flowers perfectly.

13:08.979 --> 13:11.063
Okay.

13:11.065 --> 13:14.516
It looks like a leprechaun
ate too many marshmallows.

13:14.518 --> 13:15.984
(laughing)

13:15.986 --> 13:17.152
Yes.

13:19.322 --> 13:21.073
Yes, it does.

13:21.075 --> 13:23.692
Okay, all the men coming to
your wedding should thank you.

13:23.694 --> 13:25.611
Speaking of...

13:25.613 --> 13:28.413
your dad said you're bringing
a date to dinner tonight?

13:28.415 --> 13:29.781
Oh, Evan? No, he's just
that friend

13:29.783 --> 13:31.416
that I brought
to your engagement party.

13:31.418 --> 13:33.835
Oh, yeah, that friend
that you just kiss sometimes.

13:33.837 --> 13:35.704
He kisses a lot of people.

13:35.706 --> 13:37.456
So did your dad.

13:37.458 --> 13:40.092
Wow, I really don't need to hear
the rest of that paragraph.

13:40.094 --> 13:42.210
Well, I'm just saying
when the right person

13:42.212 --> 13:44.046
comes into your life,
people can change.

13:44.048 --> 13:46.515
Let's just say
that serial dating

13:46.517 --> 13:48.300
isn't my only issue.

13:48.302 --> 13:50.385
(sighs)
Look...

13:50.387 --> 13:52.187
I'm half your dad's age.

13:52.189 --> 13:53.939
My parents
think I'm crazy.

13:53.941 --> 13:55.641
His friends think
I'm a gold digger.

13:55.643 --> 13:56.992
He has two

13:56.994 --> 13:58.760
very opinionated daughters,

13:58.762 --> 14:00.979
one of whom
is warming up to me

14:00.981 --> 14:03.282
like it's the Ice Age.

14:03.284 --> 14:06.068
On the surface
there are all these obstacles.

14:07.487 --> 14:10.072
But for the right guy,
it's worth ignoring them.

14:12.825 --> 14:14.876
(phone chimes)

14:14.878 --> 14:16.411
Oh, I'm sorry.

14:16.413 --> 14:18.380
I have to go.

14:19.165 --> 14:20.382
We'll try again later,

14:20.384 --> 14:21.717
Lucky Charms.

14:23.753 --> 14:26.138
You know, she's not so bad.

14:26.140 --> 14:28.123
I think you might need
to replace the "thingy"

14:28.125 --> 14:29.457
in "step-thingy."

14:30.343 --> 14:32.678
She left her sunglasses.

14:59.528 --> 15:02.363
You ran your
stepmom-to-be's plates?

15:02.365 --> 15:05.082
And her driver's license
and her name.

15:05.084 --> 15:07.335
Turns out she's married.
What?!

15:07.337 --> 15:09.370
I think that's the guy
who was kissing her--

15:09.372 --> 15:11.172
her husband of three years.

15:11.174 --> 15:12.373
And your dad doesn't know?

15:12.375 --> 15:13.674
He rented the Fallwyck Hotel

15:13.676 --> 15:16.294
for their wedding
six weeks from now.

15:16.296 --> 15:18.463
What do you think?

15:21.433 --> 15:24.168
Nicholas didn't
just do abstract art.

15:24.170 --> 15:25.970
He also did nudes.

15:25.972 --> 15:27.972
Yeah, don't they all.

15:27.974 --> 15:30.174
Hey, look at these.

15:33.845 --> 15:36.731
Why would you paint
the same thing over and over?

15:36.733 --> 15:38.866
To get better at it?

15:38.868 --> 15:41.285
Or sell it
more than once.

15:44.389 --> 15:48.042
There's a bunch
of duplicates here.

15:48.044 --> 15:50.711
<i>Untitled Number Three,</i>
<i>Untitled Number Three...</i>

15:50.713 --> 15:52.482
Maybe we're looking
at some kind of art fraud.

15:52.483 --> 15:54.121
Collectors think
they're getting a one of-a-kind,

15:54.122 --> 15:55.722
but Marco's
selling multiple copies

15:56.019 --> 15:57.418
of the same painting.

15:57.420 --> 15:59.754
We got to meet this Marco.
Mm.

16:04.843 --> 16:06.394
Get this.

16:06.396 --> 16:08.479
A month ago, Nicholas
sold three of his paintings

16:08.481 --> 16:10.665
to a gallery across town
for a couple hundred bucks.

16:10.667 --> 16:12.400
But Marco sells them
for thousands.

16:12.402 --> 16:13.935
Why the premium rate?

16:16.605 --> 16:18.773
Hey, check this out.

16:20.442 --> 16:22.076
List of clients?

16:22.078 --> 16:23.444
Maybe Nicholas threatened
to tell Marco's clients

16:23.446 --> 16:25.179
that they were being swindled.

16:25.181 --> 16:28.199
That much money on the line,
not a bad reason to kill him.

16:28.201 --> 16:30.234
Whoa.

16:30.236 --> 16:33.571
Assistant District Attorney Fred Simpson.
You know him?

16:33.573 --> 16:36.841
Only by reputation-- guy's
supposed to be a bulldog.

16:37.876 --> 16:39.677
TESS:
<i>So, where you been, Marco?</i>

16:39.679 --> 16:41.095
Trying to disappear?

16:41.097 --> 16:43.798
If I was trying to disappear,
I would have.

16:43.800 --> 16:47.084
I was dining in Long Island
with witnesses.

16:47.086 --> 16:49.053
Well, I understand you and
Nicholas had a pretty heated

16:49.055 --> 16:50.805
fight the other night.
Did we?

16:50.807 --> 16:53.257
Well, I guess the union
of commerce and culture

16:53.259 --> 16:55.426
is not always so unified.
Was he upset

16:55.428 --> 16:57.695
you were cheating him
out of his rightful cut?

16:58.730 --> 17:02.199
Painters loathe capitalism

17:02.201 --> 17:04.452
but they love the rewards.

17:04.454 --> 17:08.039
Or did he threaten to expose
your money laundering scam?

17:08.040 --> 17:09.624
Money laundering?
How else do you explain

17:09.626 --> 17:12.460
the prices you're getting
for Nicholas's work?

17:12.462 --> 17:14.561
Art is subjective.

17:14.564 --> 17:16.480
So is the price you pay for it.

17:16.482 --> 17:19.083
Is that what you told Assistant
District Attorney Simpson?

17:19.085 --> 17:20.685
'Cause I'm thinking you

17:20.686 --> 17:22.553
and ADA Simpson
were working together.

17:22.555 --> 17:24.472
You're mistaken.

17:24.473 --> 17:26.424
All right.

17:26.425 --> 17:29.310
Well, based on the invoices
we found in Nicholas's studio,

17:29.312 --> 17:30.845
and the duplicate paintings,

17:30.847 --> 17:33.180
we have enough to hold you
on false representation.

17:33.182 --> 17:36.067
I want my lawyer present.

17:36.069 --> 17:38.936
And I need my phone call.

17:38.938 --> 17:40.488
I have to let my curator know

17:40.490 --> 17:42.189
to cancel tonight's opening.

17:42.191 --> 17:43.908
The opening?

17:43.910 --> 17:45.526
Huh. You know,

17:45.528 --> 17:47.778
I've always been curious
about contemporary art.

17:47.780 --> 17:50.031
Oh, and I'll get right
on that phone call for you.

17:50.033 --> 17:52.533
Look at me,
running out the door.

17:52.535 --> 17:55.753
Fast as I can.

18:00.709 --> 18:04.011
Okay, I guess
there's no other way

18:04.013 --> 18:06.047
to do this than
just say it.

18:06.049 --> 18:08.799
Um...

18:08.801 --> 18:10.518
Dad, Brooke is married.

18:10.520 --> 18:12.603
(chuckles)
Is that all?

18:12.605 --> 18:14.271
Isn't that enough?

18:14.273 --> 18:15.973
It's not what you think.

18:15.975 --> 18:18.008
She's going through
a horrible divorce.

18:18.010 --> 18:21.228
Made more horrible by the fact
that she isn't divorced.

18:21.230 --> 18:22.863
Did you run
a background check on her?

18:22.865 --> 18:24.315
Yeah, but I...
Well, you know

18:24.317 --> 18:25.683
if you hadn't stopped
your research

18:25.685 --> 18:27.401
when you found
something to judge,

18:27.403 --> 18:29.036
you would have discovered
that the divorce was supposed

18:29.038 --> 18:30.538
to be finalized weeks ago.

18:30.540 --> 18:32.623
Brooke's husband's
still in love with her,

18:32.625 --> 18:34.692
so he made some
new demands, that's all.

18:34.694 --> 18:36.811
I saw them kiss.

18:39.047 --> 18:41.315
Brooke told me
that he followed her.

18:41.317 --> 18:43.200
He texted her from outside.

18:43.202 --> 18:44.969
Now I'm sure
she didn't return this kiss.

18:44.971 --> 18:46.387
Yes, she pushed him away,

18:46.389 --> 18:48.589
but she just didn't
want anyone to see.

18:48.591 --> 18:51.976
I-I think she's using you.

18:53.979 --> 18:56.580
Catherine, have you ever
stopped to ask yourself

18:56.582 --> 18:59.400
why I didn't tell you
about her divorce myself?

18:59.402 --> 19:00.868
I am worried about you.

19:00.870 --> 19:02.970
Because no one's worthy
in your eyes.

19:02.972 --> 19:08.192
Now, this judgmental attitude
may make you a good cop,

19:08.194 --> 19:10.444
but it also makes it
very difficult

19:10.446 --> 19:12.730
to have a relationship with you.

19:26.628 --> 19:28.713
Art openings are pretentious.
We just figure out

19:28.715 --> 19:31.182
where the money is coming from,
and we get out of there.

19:31.184 --> 19:33.434
TESS: Unless we meet
some handsome art lover.

19:33.436 --> 19:35.252
(chuckles)
Focus.

19:35.254 --> 19:37.204
I checked
Nicholas's credit reports.

19:37.206 --> 19:38.656
He applied for an apartment
two days ago.

19:38.658 --> 19:39.974
According to the landlady,

19:39.976 --> 19:41.559
he was gonna move in
with his girlfriend.

19:41.561 --> 19:43.894
What are you wearing, anyway?

19:43.896 --> 19:45.196
Whatever's clean.

19:45.198 --> 19:46.814
He was moving in
with a girlfriend

19:46.816 --> 19:48.733
who dumped him
two weeks earlier?

19:48.735 --> 19:50.401
That <i>is</i> wishful thinking.

19:50.403 --> 19:51.786
Hey, what are you wearing?

19:51.788 --> 19:55.456
Heather's shoes, apparently.

19:55.458 --> 19:58.159
I'll see you there.

20:06.668 --> 20:08.586
Hi.

20:08.588 --> 20:10.337
I'm in a hurry, Vincent.

20:10.339 --> 20:12.506
I'm on my way to a case.

20:14.059 --> 20:16.727
A little overdressed
for a case.

20:16.729 --> 20:18.128
Murdered painter.

20:18.130 --> 20:21.432
Going to a
gallery opening.

20:23.018 --> 20:24.802
Vincent...

20:24.804 --> 20:27.271
what are you doing here?

20:27.273 --> 20:30.741
I was just in the neighborhood.

20:30.743 --> 20:32.860
Really?

20:32.862 --> 20:35.362
Yeah.
It's just,

20:35.364 --> 20:37.164
one minute I think we're
moving in one direction,

20:37.166 --> 20:39.250
and then we're moving in another.
Catherine,

20:39.252 --> 20:40.668
I know that...

20:40.670 --> 20:43.153
you can't wait around
for me; I mean...

20:43.155 --> 20:45.706
You... you don't have
to let me down easy.

20:45.708 --> 20:47.808
I get it.

20:47.810 --> 20:50.878
You and I, this, it's just,
it's... too complicated.

20:50.880 --> 20:53.614
I don't know what I
thought, that you'd...

20:53.616 --> 20:56.016
come over for dinner
like some normal guy?

20:56.018 --> 20:58.302
I realize that was stupid of me.
It's not stupid.

20:58.304 --> 21:01.118
Look, I should've just
told you that I was okay.

21:01.218 --> 21:04.768
I was reading into our connection
like it was fate or destiny

21:04.977 --> 21:06.527
that brought us together.

21:06.529 --> 21:10.481
Truth is...
you've saved other people,

21:10.483 --> 21:13.334
not just me.

21:13.336 --> 21:16.737
We should just stick
to working on cases.

21:16.739 --> 21:18.906
That's what we are.

21:18.908 --> 21:21.025
(knocking on door)

21:21.027 --> 21:22.426
(sighs)

21:22.428 --> 21:23.894
Evan.

21:23.896 --> 21:27.331
Um... if you'll
excuse me?

21:27.333 --> 21:31.285
It's just, uh... my date.

21:42.230 --> 21:45.683
I thought I'd order the lobster
and ask for a bib.

21:45.685 --> 21:47.818
Properly mortify you
in front of your father.

21:47.820 --> 21:49.603
I'm sorry I forgot to call.

21:49.605 --> 21:51.071
Dinner is off.

21:51.073 --> 21:53.107
How come you look so stunning?

21:53.109 --> 21:55.492
Thank you. Long story.

21:55.494 --> 21:57.161
But you are off the hook.

21:57.163 --> 21:59.613
And if I don't want
to be off the hook?

21:59.615 --> 22:01.665
Well, we're
both dressed up

22:01.667 --> 22:03.450
in the most electric
city in the world.

22:03.452 --> 22:05.035
There must be
somewhere we can go.

22:05.037 --> 22:08.005
I wish that I could,
but I'm on a case.

22:08.007 --> 22:09.757
Lucky criminal.

22:09.759 --> 22:11.225
Another time?

22:11.227 --> 22:15.062
Actually, what do
you know about art?

22:17.048 --> 22:19.683
♪

22:35.867 --> 22:38.736
♪

22:54.158 --> 22:57.060
Coffee or tea?

22:57.062 --> 22:59.796
Was I supposed
to pick up something?

23:01.099 --> 23:03.316
Why are you using
my computer?

23:03.318 --> 23:05.852
I needed to find
a subway map.

23:05.854 --> 23:08.304
A lifelong New Yorker
who's part bloodhound,

23:08.306 --> 23:11.458
and you suddenly forget how
to get to Rockefeller Center?

23:11.460 --> 23:14.194
I'm going back to
the old neighborhood.

23:14.196 --> 23:15.545
Why are you going there?

23:15.547 --> 23:17.998
Oh, wait,
let me guess:

23:18.000 --> 23:19.349
Catherine.

23:19.351 --> 23:21.034
Murdered painter.

23:21.036 --> 23:24.037
The article in the newspaper
said he was from Astoria, so...

23:24.039 --> 23:26.006
(laughs)
You are so lame.

23:26.008 --> 23:27.824
Oh, as lame as you

23:27.826 --> 23:30.026
not telling me you were
going on a date with Sara?

23:30.028 --> 23:32.328
Yeah. She instant-
messaged you,

23:32.330 --> 23:34.598
was wondering
why you're late.

23:34.600 --> 23:36.967
So, you never answered: coffee or tea?
Green tea.

23:36.969 --> 23:38.813
Green tea.
Loaded with antioxidants.

23:38.838 --> 23:39.670
Look, Vincent...

23:39.671 --> 23:42.722
After all the lectures you
gave me about Catherine.

23:42.724 --> 23:44.274
But...

23:44.276 --> 23:46.059
All right, I should've
told you, just like

23:46.061 --> 23:48.111
you should tell Catherine
how you feel instead of...

23:48.113 --> 23:50.397
using a case as
an excuse to see her.

23:50.399 --> 23:52.899
No, she told me
to stick to cases.

23:53.935 --> 23:56.019
There are
two million people

23:56.021 --> 23:58.872
in Queens-- how exactly
are you planning to help?

23:58.874 --> 24:02.826
By finding the one
that knows everything.

24:21.229 --> 24:24.564
Excuse me,
is the paper still a dollar?

24:24.566 --> 24:26.266
No wonder I can't retire.

24:26.268 --> 24:27.834
It's $2.50.

24:27.836 --> 24:29.986
Is there any chance
you know the, uh,

24:29.988 --> 24:31.404
Varkas family?

24:31.406 --> 24:33.240
I just wanted to give
my condolences.

24:33.242 --> 24:34.908
Oh, yeah.
Too bad about Nick.

24:34.910 --> 24:37.444
Stopped by every day
on the way to work

24:37.446 --> 24:38.778
to buy a paper.

24:38.780 --> 24:41.248
Oh, so he worked by here?
Yeah, his mother

24:41.250 --> 24:42.916
owns the travel agency
on Steinway.

24:42.918 --> 24:44.584
He paints...

24:44.586 --> 24:46.703
uh, painted...

24:46.705 --> 24:49.289
in a studio on the top floor.
Right.

24:49.291 --> 24:50.707
Uh, thanks.

24:50.709 --> 24:53.426
Neighborhood isn't
what it used to be.

24:53.428 --> 24:55.411
Loyal customers like Varkas.

24:55.413 --> 24:57.848
People from here to Ditmars
used to stop by

24:57.850 --> 24:59.349
on the way to work.

24:59.351 --> 25:01.751
You know, you remind me
of one of them.

25:01.753 --> 25:03.553
I-I haven't been
around here before.

25:03.555 --> 25:06.139
No, who is it,
now, uh...?

25:06.141 --> 25:08.191
Michael Keller.

25:09.260 --> 25:12.529
Yeah. Any relation?

25:12.531 --> 25:14.064
Uh, no.

25:14.066 --> 25:17.150
He stopped by
on the way to work every day.

25:17.152 --> 25:19.703
Lost two sons in the Towers.

25:19.705 --> 25:23.073
One in Afghanistan.

25:23.075 --> 25:25.659
(sighs) Shame.

25:27.328 --> 25:29.412
Uh, it's-it's nice
talking to you.

25:29.414 --> 25:31.331
Thanks... thanks for the paper.

25:32.466 --> 25:35.285
♪

25:39.290 --> 25:41.457
♪ Lying on a fake beach

25:41.459 --> 25:43.894
♪ You'll never get a tan...

25:44.962 --> 25:46.296
Fancy crowd.

25:46.298 --> 25:49.132
Not your usual
money-laundering thugs.

25:50.801 --> 25:54.137
Just think, Brooke could've
put you in <i>that</i> for the wedding.

25:55.639 --> 25:56.823
I don't mind it.

25:56.825 --> 25:58.108
Evan, focus--

25:58.110 --> 25:59.776
you're supposed
to be mingling.

25:59.778 --> 26:01.695
All right, so we know
how the money gets clean.

26:01.697 --> 26:02.979
Let's figure out
why it's dirty.

26:07.318 --> 26:09.419
(clears throat)
How tall are you ?

26:09.421 --> 26:11.037
Six feet in those heels?

26:11.039 --> 26:14.624
Six one, but
who's counting?

26:14.626 --> 26:17.210
Oh. I guess you are.
(laughs): Yeah.

26:21.716 --> 26:24.634
15 grand!

26:24.636 --> 26:27.670
And I'll bet it's
worth every penny.

26:34.645 --> 26:36.646
You seem like
a wise woman...

26:36.648 --> 26:38.565
Hey...

26:38.567 --> 26:40.483
It's not art fraud.

26:40.485 --> 26:42.619
I just got
propositioned.

26:42.621 --> 26:44.638
That's because they're not
paying for the paintings.

26:44.640 --> 26:47.324
They're paying
for the women.

26:51.871 --> 26:53.657
Marco's no gallery
owner-- he's a pimp.

26:53.757 --> 26:56.136
Now we know why Nicholas knocked out
so many of the same paintings

26:56.137 --> 26:58.037
and why clients paid
so much for them.

26:58.039 --> 27:00.173
You pay big bucks for a painting,
and a woman comes home with you.

27:00.364 --> 27:02.063
Hard money trail
for the authorities to follow.

27:02.065 --> 27:04.232
Do you think Nicholas knew
his art was being used

27:04.234 --> 27:05.834
as a front
for prostitution?

27:05.836 --> 27:08.453
If he did, maybe
he was upset,

27:08.455 --> 27:10.121
and he confronted Marco,
and things didn't go so well.

27:10.123 --> 27:12.507
Ballistics just came in--
the gun that killed Nicholas

27:12.509 --> 27:13.875
was a Lady Smith.

27:13.877 --> 27:15.794
Dozens of sexy suspects,
50 johns--

27:15.796 --> 27:17.879
Vice is gonna have
a field day with this.

27:17.881 --> 27:19.914
I have to admit, this is
the best-looking room

27:19.916 --> 27:21.516
of suspects I've ever seen.
Oh, great.

27:21.518 --> 27:23.101
Then you'll have
a good time sussing out

27:23.103 --> 27:25.353
if any of them are carrying.
Or if any of them

27:25.355 --> 27:27.922
will cop to having
a relationship with Nicholas.

27:27.924 --> 27:30.525
CATHERINE:
Do you think she's in on it?

27:30.527 --> 27:33.395
One way to find out.

27:34.447 --> 27:36.147
What I love
about this painting

27:36.149 --> 27:39.284
is the youthfulness,
the freshness.

27:39.286 --> 27:41.820
As if it were uncorrupted
by the world.

27:41.822 --> 27:45.373
Excuse me for a minute.

27:45.375 --> 27:47.792
You get all that
from an orange canvas?

27:47.794 --> 27:49.244
Nicholas was gifted.

27:49.246 --> 27:51.629
What brings you by, Detective?

27:51.631 --> 27:53.248
Oh, we thought
we'd pay our respects.

27:53.250 --> 27:55.450
Obviously, we're
not the only ones.

27:55.452 --> 27:57.919
Well, people really respond
to his work.

27:57.921 --> 27:59.471
And yet this is the only gallery

27:59.473 --> 28:01.272
where Nicholas's work
sells at these prices.

28:01.274 --> 28:04.392
Well, that's Marco's gift--
making unknown artists

28:04.394 --> 28:06.394
into stars.

28:06.396 --> 28:07.729
(sighs)

28:07.731 --> 28:10.365
I wish Nicholas was here
to enjoy it.

28:11.517 --> 28:14.102
Excuse me.

28:17.506 --> 28:19.574
♪

28:19.576 --> 28:21.076
Good evening.

28:26.665 --> 28:29.334
CATHERINE:
A girl's gotta earn a living,

28:29.336 --> 28:32.954
but nights like these,
I wish I was out of the game.

28:32.956 --> 28:34.089
I'm Cat.

28:34.091 --> 28:35.623
Daphne.

28:35.625 --> 28:37.625
And there's nowhere to go.

28:37.627 --> 28:40.211
At least with these guys,
you know where you stand.

28:40.213 --> 28:43.715
Maybe, but I'm still holding
out for Prince Charming.

28:43.717 --> 28:46.267
If you're looking for love,
take it from me--

28:46.269 --> 28:48.103
it never works out.

28:48.105 --> 28:50.055
Prince Charming is a liar.

28:50.057 --> 28:53.341
I can't believe the
artist died in here.

28:53.343 --> 28:55.193
Did you know him?
I heard that

28:55.195 --> 28:58.797
he was in love with
one of the girls.

28:58.799 --> 29:02.534
I met him... once or twice.

29:02.536 --> 29:03.902
Acted like he was
a sensitive artist,

29:03.904 --> 29:05.954
but he was "in love"
with a lot of girls.

29:05.956 --> 29:09.874
Really? I heard over
at the bar that he, uh,

29:09.876 --> 29:12.007
applied for an apartment
two days ago,

29:12.032 --> 29:13.660
wanted to move
in with his girlfriend.

29:15.581 --> 29:17.966
I hadn't heard that.

29:21.504 --> 29:23.388
Excuse me.
You know they don't like it

29:23.390 --> 29:25.757
when we stand in
one place for too long.

29:30.563 --> 29:32.547
EVAN:
Where's Tess?

29:32.549 --> 29:36.434
Either with the man of her dreams
or calling Vice-- your guess.

29:36.436 --> 29:38.603
Making me talk to
other women all night,

29:38.605 --> 29:41.055
it's a strange tactic,
but a memorable one.

29:44.560 --> 29:47.695
CATHERINE: Evan, can you just
excuse me for a second?

29:48.230 --> 29:50.832
♪

29:56.806 --> 29:59.174
What are you doing here?

30:05.381 --> 30:07.715
Are you okay?

30:07.717 --> 30:09.300
I needed to see you.

30:09.302 --> 30:11.853
I'm working.

30:11.855 --> 30:13.605
Well, that's why I'm here.

30:13.607 --> 30:17.525
The, uh, murdered painter,
I found his studio and...

30:17.527 --> 30:19.077
You what?

30:19.079 --> 30:21.830
Well, you said stick to cases.
I didn't mean

30:21.832 --> 30:25.500
for you to break and enter
a victim's private property.

30:25.502 --> 30:27.836
Did you see the paintings?

30:27.838 --> 30:29.937
Vincent, the paintings
don't matter.

30:29.939 --> 30:33.091
It's just all a cover for
a high-end escort service.

30:33.093 --> 30:35.510
Come with me.

30:38.814 --> 30:41.449
♪

30:43.502 --> 30:44.636
Her name's Daphne.

30:44.638 --> 30:46.337
I talked to her
at the gallery.

30:46.339 --> 30:49.641
She seemed...
jaded, bitter.

30:49.643 --> 30:51.843
Or heartbroken.

30:53.596 --> 30:57.482
Nicholas's mom said that his
girlfriend broke up with him.

30:57.484 --> 31:00.735
Maybe Daphne is
just his model.

31:00.737 --> 31:04.906
VINCENT: It may have started that way,
but it became more.

31:07.026 --> 31:11.696
And look at the way
he... captured her.

31:11.698 --> 31:14.249
The curve of her back.

31:14.251 --> 31:15.533
The softness

31:15.535 --> 31:17.902
of her skin.

31:19.538 --> 31:23.791
He spent every waking moment
painting her.

31:23.793 --> 31:26.961
She was in every brush stroke.

31:32.868 --> 31:36.354
I know I'm not
the detective here, but...

31:36.356 --> 31:40.191
this man, he loved this woman.

31:40.193 --> 31:41.726
Now, maybe there
was someone else,

31:41.728 --> 31:43.962
someone that didn't want them
to be together.

31:43.964 --> 31:46.180
But they weren't together.

31:46.182 --> 31:49.100
She said he loved
a lot of girls.

31:49.102 --> 31:52.186
I find that
hard to believe.

31:53.289 --> 31:55.623
You know, maybe
she doubted him.

31:55.625 --> 31:59.377
The way he felt about her.

31:59.379 --> 32:03.781
But if he loved her so much...

32:03.783 --> 32:06.751
why did she push him away?

32:06.753 --> 32:10.088
She didn't feel worthy.

32:10.090 --> 32:13.841
How can you be so sure?

32:13.843 --> 32:18.429
'Cause I know
what it feels like.

32:22.351 --> 32:24.068
♪ But I'm

32:24.070 --> 32:27.772
♪ Still trying

32:34.697 --> 32:36.931
♪ Oh, oh

32:36.933 --> 32:39.367
♪

32:41.086 --> 32:43.204
♪ Oh, oh...

32:49.094 --> 32:50.617
TESS:
Hey, who's Daphne Finnerty?

32:50.618 --> 32:51.950
Nicholas's girlfriend--
those paintings

32:51.952 --> 32:53.735
in the studio, all of her.

32:53.737 --> 32:54.953
Was she at the gallery tonight?

32:54.955 --> 32:56.538
Yeah. She said
she barely knew the guy.

32:56.540 --> 32:58.073
But when I mentioned
the apartment that he leased,

32:58.075 --> 32:59.625
she took off.
I don't think she realized

32:59.627 --> 33:01.243
he wanted to move in with her.

33:01.245 --> 33:03.161
Well, if she was his girlfriend,
wouldn't she know?

33:03.163 --> 33:05.196
Unless someone made her doubt
that he loved her.

33:05.198 --> 33:07.532
And the person who
wouldn't want her to move in

33:07.534 --> 33:09.051
with her boyfriend is her pimp.

33:09.053 --> 33:10.502
No, try madame--
Lauren, the curator,

33:10.504 --> 33:12.087
she conveniently left
the gallery

33:12.089 --> 33:14.306
right after she saw me.
Makes sense.

33:14.308 --> 33:16.374
Found this at the studio.

33:16.376 --> 33:18.093
People are supposed to use
those when they move art.

33:18.095 --> 33:20.211
Yeah, "people" as in a curator
with a gallery show.

33:20.213 --> 33:21.597
Could explain our white fibers.

33:21.599 --> 33:23.765
I had a unit put on
Lauren's apartment.

33:23.767 --> 33:26.318
Our conniving curator got
home ten minutes ago.

33:26.320 --> 33:28.820
Anyone else enter the building
in the last ten minutes?

33:28.822 --> 33:30.272
Yeah, a woman, early 20s.

33:30.274 --> 33:32.991
Green dress?
Yeah.

33:34.744 --> 33:37.228
LAUREN: Just calm down.
We can talk this through.

33:37.230 --> 33:38.664
DAPHNE:
You lied to me!

33:38.666 --> 33:40.249
LAUREN:
I was protecting you!

33:40.251 --> 33:42.751
That's Lauren's apartment.

33:42.753 --> 33:45.587
DAPHNE: He was the best thing
that ever happened to me!

33:45.589 --> 33:47.339
The only man
that I ever loved!

33:47.341 --> 33:48.757
LAUREN:
I know you're upset.

33:48.759 --> 33:50.959
NYPD! Open up!

33:50.961 --> 33:54.212
DAPHNE: He's dead, and I
can never get him back!

33:54.214 --> 33:55.580
LAUREN: It's been
a terrible shock,

33:55.582 --> 34:00.418
but I swear I had nothing
to do with this, Daphne.

34:00.420 --> 34:02.554
Drop your weapon!
Daphne, don't do this.

34:02.556 --> 34:03.689
You couldn't stand
the thought

34:03.691 --> 34:05.607
that I might actually be happy.

34:05.609 --> 34:06.892
Nicholas wouldn't want this
for you.

34:06.894 --> 34:09.478
She told me I was
just a call girl,

34:09.480 --> 34:11.362
that I meant nothing
to him,

34:11.364 --> 34:13.764
that I wasn't worthy of love.

34:13.766 --> 34:15.367
He was gonna leave you anyways.

34:15.369 --> 34:16.601
They always do.

34:16.603 --> 34:18.268
And Lauren didn't want
to miss one

34:18.271 --> 34:20.205
of her best moneymakers,
isn't that right?

34:20.206 --> 34:22.157
He swore to me he wasn't
sleeping with any of the other girls,

34:22.159 --> 34:24.493
but I didn't believe him
because of your lies.

34:24.495 --> 34:26.110
Nicholas knew he had to get
Daphne away from you.

34:26.112 --> 34:27.629
That's what that phone
call was about;

34:27.630 --> 34:28.996
not the price of the paintings,

34:28.998 --> 34:30.281
but the price
of Daphne's freedom.

34:30.283 --> 34:32.384
What?
It's not true.

34:32.386 --> 34:34.719
But he didn't have the money
to buy her out,

34:34.722 --> 34:36.121
so what did he do, Lauren,

34:36.123 --> 34:37.806
threaten to expose
the entire operation?

34:37.808 --> 34:39.558
Turn over that client list?

34:41.811 --> 34:44.846
I wasn't gonna jeopardize
everything for a stupid whore.

34:44.848 --> 34:46.063
You killed him!

34:46.065 --> 34:47.683
And if you kill her,

34:47.685 --> 34:49.400
you will be
throwing your life away.

34:49.402 --> 34:52.521
Daphne, Nicholas, he...

34:52.523 --> 34:55.690
he saw your true worth.

34:55.693 --> 34:58.527
He did.
He loved you.

35:01.447 --> 35:04.315
He loved you.

35:04.317 --> 35:07.035
Put the gun down.

35:10.256 --> 35:13.041
Put down your gun.

35:22.135 --> 35:24.302
(sighs)

35:41.320 --> 35:42.788
Daphne won't be charged.

35:42.790 --> 35:44.539
I just got off
the phone with the DA's Office.

35:44.541 --> 35:45.874
They agreed that her statement
will help make

35:45.876 --> 35:47.626
the murder and pandering
charges stick.

35:47.628 --> 35:49.211
Nice work, partner.
Thanks. Hey, I'll buy you

35:49.213 --> 35:50.579
a beer if you buy me one.

35:50.581 --> 35:52.581
You are on. I just need
to do a couple things.

35:52.583 --> 35:54.082
I'll meet you in, like, an hour?
Yeah.

35:54.084 --> 35:55.634
Careful. Last time I made plans
with Catherine,

35:55.636 --> 35:56.918
I ended up in a bordello.

35:56.920 --> 35:58.553
I'm gonna finish
my report...

35:58.555 --> 36:00.538
over there, by myself.

36:01.557 --> 36:03.725
Congratulations,
Detective Chandler.

36:03.727 --> 36:05.043
And if I haven't
said it already,

36:05.045 --> 36:06.645
you were great last night.

36:06.647 --> 36:08.563
Not quite the undercover
experience that I'm used to,

36:08.565 --> 36:10.649
but I think I acquitted
myself quite nicely.

36:10.651 --> 36:12.934
I think you enjoyed yourself
a little too much.

36:12.936 --> 36:15.053
Well, I could say
the same for you.

36:15.055 --> 36:18.240
I saw you slip out of
the gallery with someone.

36:18.242 --> 36:20.108
That was just a john
I was interviewing.

36:20.110 --> 36:21.860
He said he knew
everything about the scheme,

36:21.862 --> 36:23.278
but he didn't want
anyone to overhear.

36:23.280 --> 36:25.396
Funny, I didn't peg him
as a client.

36:25.398 --> 36:28.033
He shows up to an upscale escort
party wearing street clothes

36:28.035 --> 36:30.435
and the only woman he wanted
to talk to is you.

36:30.437 --> 36:34.790
Evan, a certain kind of woman
would take that as an insult.

36:34.792 --> 36:38.260
Then let me make it up to you.
Dinner, no chaperone.

36:38.262 --> 36:41.246
I think I'm gonna have
to take a rain check.

36:41.248 --> 36:44.466
Has to rain sometime, Cat.
I'll wait.

36:44.468 --> 36:46.384
You're very confident.

36:46.386 --> 36:49.137
And patient.

37:00.366 --> 37:02.317
You look beautiful.

37:02.319 --> 37:04.653
What are you doing here?

37:04.655 --> 37:07.873
I... owe you an apology.

37:07.875 --> 37:09.825
You think?

37:09.827 --> 37:11.793
Yes. I made, like,
a hundred assumptions

37:11.795 --> 37:13.779
and I acted like an idiot.

37:13.781 --> 37:17.549
A huge, jumbo-sized idiot.

37:19.001 --> 37:21.452
But you wouldn't have had
to make so many assumptions

37:21.454 --> 37:24.172
if I'd just been honest.

37:24.174 --> 37:27.008
Your approval means
a lot to your dad.

37:29.779 --> 37:34.316
Anyone would be lucky to have
you as part of their family.

37:34.318 --> 37:37.602
(both laugh gently)

37:42.808 --> 37:44.593
CATHERINE:
<i>I waited all night for you.</i>

37:47.113 --> 37:49.414
When I left--

37:49.416 --> 37:52.100
No, not, not tonight,

37:52.102 --> 37:55.770
um, when you didn't
show up for dinner.

37:58.758 --> 38:00.091
But it seems like that's what

38:00.093 --> 38:02.661
I do the most
with my time these days...

38:02.663 --> 38:06.298
wait for the next moment
I get to see you.

38:08.968 --> 38:14.022
Vincent, it never even occurred
to me that you didn't know

38:14.024 --> 38:16.775
that you are the best
thing in my life right now.

38:19.362 --> 38:21.646
I guess seeing me kiss
another guy

38:21.648 --> 38:23.481
doesn't really help my chances.

38:23.483 --> 38:25.350
(both laugh quietly)

38:28.454 --> 38:31.756
I don't know how to do this.

38:31.758 --> 38:34.910
(sighs)

38:36.746 --> 38:40.215
You know, that, uh,

38:40.217 --> 38:45.020
artist's studio was, like, six
blocks from where I grew up.

38:45.022 --> 38:47.589
Being back there
kind of got me thinking

38:47.591 --> 38:49.874
about who I used to be.

38:51.710 --> 38:53.395
You know, if that
Vincent Keller

38:53.397 --> 38:55.096
had seen you with
another guy,

38:55.098 --> 38:56.398
he probably would've, uh...

38:56.400 --> 38:59.768
smacked him square
in the mouth.

38:59.770 --> 39:01.653
(chuckles)

39:01.655 --> 39:05.073
Does it make me a terrible
person to admit that I'm glad

39:05.075 --> 39:06.741
the thought crossed your mind?

39:06.743 --> 39:08.977
No.

39:12.365 --> 39:16.151
Who I am makes everything seem
impossible.

39:16.153 --> 39:18.203
No.

39:20.840 --> 39:23.675
Who you are...

39:23.677 --> 39:27.128
it makes everything worth it.

39:32.468 --> 39:34.686
Vincent, I have to go.

39:58.377 --> 40:00.378
(gasping)

40:09.305 --> 40:11.056
(gasping)

40:11.058 --> 40:13.591
(siren wails in distance)

